Master Data Service provides a RESTful API that systems can use to consume the tree view data [Introduction - Nexteer EA Technical Knowledge]. Developers, both Function Administrators and Normal Users, can create API for RESTful and OData endpoints. The Master Data Service Function Admin can see all users API keys (these are encrypted), but only the key's owner can delete or copy the real key value [MasterDataService - Nexteer EA Technical Knowledge-merged-0.pdf].

An example of how to use the API was provided in the same document. For instance, to make a request to the OData endpoint, you need to add an api-key or access token in the header of your request. Here is an example:

```
var client = new RestClient("https://nxt-mfgmds-dev-na-wa.azurewebsites.net/odata/TcmEntities?$filter=Type eq 'Site'");
client.Timeout = -1;
var request = new RestRequest(Method.GET);
request.AddHeader("api-key", "fake-token- >>>>>>>>>r4pQACAmffWHPzXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXJGynTc7If2mjdpAGsRNO2E9VyFQ");
IRestResponse response = client.Execute(request);
Console.WriteLine(response.Content);
```

This is an example only, and you should replace the "fake-token" with your actual api-key [MasterDataService - Nexteer EA Technical Knowledge-merged-0.pdf].

